        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">What is the best egg substitute for baking?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">The best egg substitute depends on the recipe. For binding, use 1 tablespoon ground flaxseed mixed with 3 tablespoons water per egg. For moisture and richness, use ¼ cup unsweetened applesauce or mashed banana per egg. For leavening in cakes, use ¼ teaspoon baking soda plus 1 tablespoon vinegar. Commercial egg replacers like Bob's Red Mill also work well across most recipes.</div>
        </div>
